		<a name="35536"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/04/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 22:23:39</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=782"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=782')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=35536&amp;TOPIC_ID=4442&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=57hitting+Monk+vs+63+hitting+Spec+%28Monk+Won+%2E%2E%2E%2E%2E%29&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I'd agree with everyone here about the spec pet being better because it's rarer and costlier, had we still been under the system we were pre-50.</P><P>I am absolutely and totally against the idea of having specialized pets if the EoT will own them all.  Make ALL pets, right now, warrior pets - weaker versions of the EoT.  That'll make it logical, reasonable, and consistent.  I never agreed with the idea of specialized pets if VI is going to implement them at different levels, but I sure as hell am going to support them if VI don't plan to change them back.</P><P>The people who claim that the EoT should be the hands down best pet aren't getting the bigger picture.  You are not realizing that by saying that the EoT should be the ultimate pet, you are essentially forcing every necro pre-59 or those who have not obtained EoT to be TOTALLY SUBPAR compared to mages in terms of pet power.  A level 51 mage earth pet now hits for 60+.(please note: mages also receive their "specialized" pets at different levels)  The necro's pets doesn't even come close till EoT.  There thus rises a HUGE gap in power between level 58 and level 59 necros that isn't even close to being balanced.  Already we have such a level between 59 and 60, but at least 59 and 60 is the "final" level and should mean something big, but now we'll differentiate the pre-59 necros from the post-59 necros too? That's sh*tty balance and if I ever cared about EQ as a game I would never support it.</P><P>The monk pet should've never tanked as well as the EoT.  That was a mistake comparable to having casters being so much better than melees pre-Kunark.  But let's not make the same mistake twice that happened post-Kunark when the pendulum virtually made a 180 and ended up overpowering melees.  The monk and rogue pet were meant to be situational pets and should be used as such.  They represent a sense of diversity that EQ has sadly lacked - and they should remain that way.  There is no point in obtaining either the rogue or monk pet if EoT is superior in every way - I hate having useless spells, don't you?</P><P>And please don't justify it with the statement: "well the people who don't have EoT should just PL to 60."  I'm sick and tired of people who are only concerned about the game at 60, because a (good) game is supposed to be fun and BALANCED at every level, not just 60.  </P><P>There is only one argument that I will take on seriously, because it is the only argument that I think holds any water at all:</P><P>"The rarer/costlier pet should be better."</P><P>Agreed.  The EoT SHOULD be better, but not at everything.  The mage epic pet is not better at everything.  A mage cannot chain-cast epic pets effectively, nor will he whip out the epic pet if he's in need of a rooter (the epic only stuns), or if he needs a pet immune to fire or resistant to poison.  We're talking about the epic here - not just your average run of the mill higher-level pet.  VI has gotten it right with mages - different pets for different situations (now if they can just fix the post-50 fire pet...) There is no reason why they shouldn't do it with necros.</P><P>I'm not saying that the monk pet should beat the EoT in a duel.  The EoT should have alot more hps, alot better taunt, special abilities and considerable damage potential compared to the mage level 60 tanking pet.  But there needs to be an incentive to use the other pets - I don't care what (but please don't say to conserve peridots), but there's a *reason* why the rogue and monk pets originally had better damage than the EoT and it was a good reason in my mind.  The EoT should be powerful, deserving of its title as the final necro pet, but it should not be all-powerful, just as Funeral Pyre is not all-powerful on its own, just as Touch of Night is not always better than deflux, just as trepidation is not necessarily as good as fear, just as enslave death is not always better than thrall of bones.  They're different spells, folks.  We're NOT under the linear pet evolution of the pre-50's anymore, and that's critical, because till we return to that system, there is no justification for having one all-powerful pet.</P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

