         Quite honestly, situational pets might have been useful had they been implemented from day 1.</P><P>A necro gets used to his pet being able to take a beating from 1-49.  At 53, they take a step backwards.  The ONLY option for a necro at 53 is to fear kite, that's it.  If you wanna use a pet, that's how you're using your blue pet.  This is why so many necros have switched to root/rot.  53 and 56 pets are crap, they don't have the versatility that the 49 and 59 pets have.  Yeah, it was nice to see my pet backstab when I was fear kiting in skyfire because that's the only place there was for XP when kunark came out.  yeah, it was cool to have a pet that flying kicked, but now that they fucked up pet models, no one even thinks that's cool anymore.  It's cool for about 2 days, and then you wish you just had a good ol reliable upgrade to the 49 pet.</P><P>I don't think it's an exaggeration to say that almost EVERYONE here who is over 58, used their 49 pet for some situation when they were level 58.  How is that cool?  Do mages use the 49 earth pet at level 58 EVER?</P><P>The point is, they tried to make 53 and 56 situational, but instead they made them weak crap useful in only a couple circumstances, which is more annoying than anything.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
